		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>AAs<br />
<br />
I guess first, general type AAs:<br />
<br />
An AA that allows us to carry two more tier 1 inventory slots (bag spaces).  There are an increasingly enormous number of clickies, potions, reagents, junk etc that need to be carried around today.  This should probably be given as a part of the expansion, but if not, add them as AAs.<br />
<br />
Innate Ultravision.  I don't really care, I play a dark elf wizard.  I have never worried about it, but I know many other people have.  If somehow miraculously you can gain the innate ability to see invisible things, you ought to be able to see in the dark.<br />
<br />
Hit us with another spell gem, can always find something to throw in there.<br />
<br />
Wizard type AAs:<br />
<br />
Cold based version of pyromancy.  300ish damage per tick, 30% slow.  Skip the snare part, it makes too many mobs immune to the slow part that goes along with effects like clinging frost.  30% slow is the equivalent of like a level 30 shaman.  It isn't much, but better than nothing.<br />
<br />
Magic Based version of pyromancy.  400ish damage per tick, 0 sec stun each tick.<br />
<br />
(My thoughts on pyromancy-like effects:  Each effect should give damage and provide some type of utility.  The exchange for such is a cost in agro.  This is just my opinion though, tweak as necessary to fit the individuals view on agro vs utility.)<br />
<br />
Upgrades to harvests.  Don't give us a new harvest, just AAs that increase the returns on the ones we have by 25/50/100%.<br />
<br />
Spell strikethrough.<br />
<br />
Increased chance to proc spell effects such as pyromancy, gift of mana and weave of power.<br />
<br />
Fire mastery.  +100/200/400 to base damage of fire spells.<br />
<br />
Ice mastery.  +50/100/250 to base damage of ice spells.<br />
<br />
Magic mastery.  +75/150/300 to base damage of magic spells.<br />
<br />
Improved spell casting subtlety.  Hopefully at least another 10% reduction.  (side note: Freaking fix SCS and concussion/mind crash already, it's been 2 years as &quot;other things have higher priority&quot;.  That's ridiculous, change the code so that it calculates the number, assigns it an absolute value and then makes the value negative.  Trust us, it won't be that huge of a thing that wizards will get a little kicker to concussion from that.)<br />
<br />
An AA that extends rains to four, then five pulses.  (side note:  Allow all our spells to be focused by damage modifiers please.  It's no more overpowering than the huge focii that necromancers get for their DoTs, and rains are much more cumbersome to use than DoT's.)<br />
<br />
New lines of familiars.  Primary familiar should be at least 15 mana per tick regen.  Do whatever amount of focus effect on the damage ones that is appropriate.<br />
<br />
An AA that shares familiar effects with the group would be nice, but that would be like an aura I suppose.<br />
<br />
Fix Strong Root.  36 minute refresh on it after spending all those AAs, and then giving shaman a poison based root with knockback refreshing every 3 minutes for much less is pretty unbalancing for price paid in AAs.  Don't nerf them, fix us.<br />
<br />
Some type of DPS &quot;discipline&quot; type AA to compliment FD/PD.  For instance, 36 minute refresh time, when used locks out FD/PD as well (this isn't quite right, I have to think about how to make it work better).  The effect would be:  For1 minute, all spells cost half mana.  The thinking behind this:  on a 72 minute timer, you would be able to use Prolonged Destruction to cause a great deal of damage at the sacrifice of mana (short burst fights), and then you would also be able to use this other Efficiency Based AA on a DIFFERENT fight to extend how long you could maintain a normal burn (sustained DPS fights).  I didn't explain this perfectly, but I hope someone gets the point.<br />
<br />
For my own crazy invention AA/spell:  I would like to see an AA/spell that allows a temporary (5 minute) bind.  This would allow you to drop the temporary bind, run and grab something/someone you forgot etc, and then come right back.  Would also allow abscond to become a semi-viable agro dropping tool in exchange for giving up the loading time for zoning.  Probably would need a decently long refresh timer (30 minutes maybe?).<br />
<br />
<br />
Spells:<br />
<br />
Only going into Utility here, since damage spells will most likely be scaled however the developers want anyways to fit &quot;class balance&quot;.<br />
<br />
Time for a new snare spell, we're 9 expansions out of date on ours.<br />
<br />
I like the Spellshield for DoTs idea.  Also time for a new spellshield, it is 7 expansions out of date.<br />
<br />
Group invisibility.  Plane shift by it's name sounds well within the wizards capability to make the whole group invisible, so let's make it so.  [Side note, let's drop the group only invisibility rule.  The reason it was placed in game (griefing of pet classes) has been fixed.]<br />
<br />
That's all I can think of for now.  My last plea would be to not take these ideas and hand them out to other classes after we come up with them.  Like spell haste given to clerics, mana flare given to enchanters, group mana regeneration kicker given to enchanters (PoR aura is the group familiar idea presented here months ago).  All those other classes already have much more to offer to a group already than we do.  Please don't take the utility that could be given to wizards and farm it away to other classes again.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
